lown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"349e96029908cc6c4566aa7f9e29a29a63d64f95","tid":1438044,"uid":121146,"like":6,"dislike":0,"score":6,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-08-09T16:54:43.000Z","msg":"支拿玩撚大左喇<br />\n選舉年  諗住撚侵侵撚到佢選唔到<br />\n你估侵侵唔知咩 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n你交唔到貨  佢咪打到你仆直  永不超生  再選囉"},{"pid":"00d5536765ade58b0f4388af275bbecea7244943","tid":1438044,"uid":53612,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-08-09T17:01:26.000Z","msg":"彈出彈入"},{"pid":"ebd950d39097b0cb82f95715011c38fed3f68e7f","tid":1438044,"uid":134071,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-08-09T23:45:57.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/en/component/k2/1473733-20190809.htm?share=facebook\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.rthk.hk%2Frthk%2Fen%2Fcomponent%2Fk2%2F1473733-20190809.htm%3Fshare%3Dfacebook&d=8kP02BZom8b0sC5RUQuyVQKWJX65Gw4YGtkQ1cmlXhw%3D&h=668c9def\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.rthk.hk%2Frthk%2Fen%2Fcomponent%2Fk2%2F1473733-20190809.htm%3Fshare%3Dfacebook&h=3008177e\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/en/component/k2/1473733-20190809.htm?share=facebook</a><br />\n<br />\n Trump may call off trade talks with Beijing<br />\n2019-08-09 HKT 23:34<br />\n<br />\nUS President Donald Trump said on Friday that he was not ready to finalise a trade deal with Beijing and signaled he might cancel talks set for September, raising the stakes in the intensifying Sino-US trade war.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;We'll see whether or not we keep our meeting in September,&quot; Trump told reporters at the White House before heading out on vacation at his New Jersey golf resort.<br />\n<br />\nRelations have soured further in the past week after Trump announced a new round of punitive tariffs on Chinese goods, despite a truce agreed with President Xi Jinping, and Beijing responded by halting all purchases of US agricultural goods.<br />\n<br />\nThe US Treasury then declared China a currency manipulator, after the yuan lost value in the face of the new round of tariffs due to take effect September 1.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;We're not ready to make a deal but we'll see what happens,&quot; Trump said. &quot;We have all the cards. We're doing well.&quot;<br />\n<br />\nUS and Chinese negotiators met in Shanghai late last month for the first time since talks collapsed in May, and were due to hold another round in September.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Whether or not they're canceled, we'll see,&quot; Trump said. (AFP)"},{"pid":"5bcd85ec0ccb06ff739442f09be43fd93ba22fda","tid":1438044,"uid":276989,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-08-09T23:50:03.000Z","msg":"好波 熊過夜<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/run.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"12ce382f188953143061ee0419c6bec55b0398e7","tid":1438044,"uid":24140,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-08-10T01:17:39.000Z","msg":"Trump : thank you, Hong Kong"}]}